    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Clinical diagnosis\nPCR for norovirus available but rarely used\nEvaluate for other causes of symptoms\nEvaluate for\nhypovolemia\n,\nelectrolyte abnormalities\n(e.g. BMP, electrolytes)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "hypovolemia",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Hypovolemia"
        },
        {
          "text": "electrolyte abnormalities",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Electrolyte_abnormalities"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Supportive\nIVF\nor\noral rehydration therapy\nAntiemetics\n, antidiarrheals\nGood hygiene super important for preventing spread!!!\nVirus shed in stool for up to 2 weeks after symptoms resolved\nVirus can be aerosolized during vomiting or flushing toilet\nWash hands with soap and water",
